The paper proposes a visual navigation framework that combines learning-based and model-based approaches, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for waypoint prediction, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of HJ reachability analysis, which is a mathematical optimization technique (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for navigation (cs.AI) and discusses the advantages of the proposed approach (cs.LG).
